*lirc-0.9.4a-r1 (30 Jul 2016)

  30 Jul 2016; David Seifert <soap@gentoo.org> +files/irexec-initd-0.9.4a-r1,
  +files/lirc-0.9.4-doc-path-fix.patch, +lirc-0.9.4a-r1.ebuild:
  0.9.4a-r1 fix documentation and socket directories

  set localstatedir to /var so lirc correctly uses /var/run instead of
  /var/lib/run
  install documentation to /usr/share/doc/lirc-${PF}
  use irexec-initd-0.9.4a-r1 instead of irexec-initd as the irexec initd
  script to resolve a QA notice

  Gentoo-bug: 589246
  Closes: https://github.com/gentoo/gentoo/pull/1922

  Signed-off-by: David Seifert <soap@gentoo.org>

